00:01:47,410 --> 00:01:51,390
  I, Ling Yue, promise to rent this house

22
00:01:51,390 --> 00:01:53,850
 to Miss Gu Anxin exclusively.

23
00:01:53,850 --> 00:01:56,800
  I promise to never raise the rent or sell it.

24
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,900
  If the terms of the contract are violated,

25
00:01:58,900 --> 00:02:01,320
  I will voluntarily lose all of my rights to the ownership of this house.

26
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:04,220
 The house will be returned to Miss Anxin.

27
00:02:04,220 --> 00:02:07,930
Aren't the terms of this contract written too unfairly for you?

28
00:02:07,930 --> 00:02:11,390
I'm the landlord. You're paying me rent. It's very fair.

29
00:02:11,390 --> 00:02:14,170
It's just like this IOU letter. Back then, I took advantage of you.

30
00:02:14,170 --> 00:02:16,210
Now it's your turn.

31
00:02:17,570 --> 00:02:19,440
Thank you.

32
00:02:21,930 --> 00:02:23,850
This is where our relationship began.

33
00:02:23,850 --> 00:02:25,980
Now, it is where our relationship continues.

34
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:29,980
We will hug each other closely and never separate again.

35
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:58,260
Let's go home.

36
00:02:58,260 --> 00:02:59,940
Wait.

37
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:06,080
We are an official couple now. Asking for a good-night kiss isn't going too far, is it?

38
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:19,140
You should go home and rest early.

39
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:21,090
Then, I'll come to pick you up tomorrow.  Good night.

40
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:22,760
Good night.

41
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,760
Wait a second.

42
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,500
Good night.

43
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:35,340
Good night, Elder Brother-in-Law.

44
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,040
Who's his brother-in-law?

45
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:44,240
Come on. Let's go home!

46
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,760
We're leaving.

47
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:48,830
- He hugged me. 
 - He likes you.

48
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:00,900
Brother, cool down your anger.

49
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,960
Want some beer?

50
00:04:06,230 --> 00:04:08,160
You and Ling Yue, what...

51
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:11,390
Did you agree to be with him so easily?

52
00:04:12,370 --> 00:04:14,960
It's... It's just a kind of feeling

53
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:19,580
called an "inexplicable work of outer forces." I don't know whether or not you know. 
  (T/N: Literally, "the work of gods and demons". It's the feeling where one believes their actions are being controlled not by their own will)

54
00:04:20,410 --> 00:04:22,640
  You really have fallen in love with him.

55
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:39,800
Brother, I heard about it.

56
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,730
Youyou told me what happened yesterday.

57
00:04:41,730 --> 00:04:43,860
Yesterday, she might have been a li-li-little nervous—

58
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:45,320
Don't use Youyou to change the subject.

59
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:48,550
Exactly what is going on between you and Ling Yue?

60
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:52,120
It's exactly what you saw.

61
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:54,810
No, Brother. Ling Yue and his family are all very good people.

62
00:04:54,810 --> 00:04:58,320
Other than... Other than his elder brother... Ling-Ling-Ling Ling Fang,

63
00:04:58,320 --> 00:05:00,600
everyone else is really great.

64
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:04,130
You know that they're good just after meeting them once?

65
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:08,650
Looks like you've really fallen too deep.

66
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:19,560
If you really like him that much,

67
00:05:20,670 --> 00:05:23,550
I'm willing to let you two give it a try.

68
00:05:23,550 --> 00:05:25,760
But you have to agree to one condition.

69
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:30,660
If he mistreats you, you must tell me.

70
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:33,600
No matter what, you can't let yourself suffer.

71
00:05:37,010 --> 00:05:38,760
I understand.

72
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:41,170
I just know you are the best.

73
00:05:43,940 --> 00:05:45,820
Where's your bracelet?

74
00:05:45,820 --> 00:05:48,380
When I was leaving the house, I put it in its box.

75
00:05:48,380 --> 00:05:50,880
You'd better wear it. If you do, I'll feel more at ease.

76
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:54,210
It doesn't matter. I rarely have nightmares anymore.

77
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:57,180
Really?

78
00:05:58,320 --> 00:06:00,300
You've worn it for so many years.

79
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,970
Suddenly, there comes a day when you don't need it anymore.

80
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:05,370
- What? 
 - Nothing.

81
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:11,320
By the way, I have one more thing to tell you.

82
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:16,350
I'm getting ready to move back to Barberry Lane.

83
00:06:16,350 --> 00:06:19,210
- W-Wasn't that apartment sold? 
 - Yes, it was.

84
00:06:19,210 --> 00:06:23,320
But the new owner is still planning to rent it out.

85
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:26,870
I made it in time and met with him.

86
00:06:26,870 --> 00:06:30,440
If this new landlord pushes you out with no notice just like the last one, what will you do then?

87
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:32,160
He won't.

88
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:36,940
This homeowner and I signed a... very special contract.

89
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:39,360
I won't get kicked out. Don't worry.

90
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,950
You just moved in and now you're leaving.

91
00:06:42,660 --> 00:06:44,870
Do you really like that place so much?

92
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:49,060
That place truly isn't as nice as yours,

93
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:51,210
and it's not as comfortable,

94
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:53,490
but I really have gotten used to it.

95
00:06:53,490 --> 00:06:59,550
Besides, there, I have some very, very, very precious memories.

96
00:07:05,090 --> 00:07:07,080
Brother, I'm just moving.

97
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,690
You don't need to treat it like we will never see each other again.

98
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:11,980
You can come and see me whenever you feel like it.

99
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:15,410
I can also come over here to see you often.

100
00:07:15,410 --> 00:07:18,380
But... I've already grown up.

101
00:07:18,380 --> 00:07:20,100
I can't always live at your house.

102
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:23,080
You can always live at my house.

103
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:29,640
Okay, okay, okay.

104
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:34,210
I'll help you whenever you want to move.

105
00:07:38,310 --> 00:07:41,180
Hello. I'm here to help Miss Anxin move.

106
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:02,060
Ai Li, I've caused you a lot of trouble today. You've worked hard. Thank you so much.

107
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:03,880
It's nothing. It's my job.

108
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,930
President Ling originally planned to come personally today,

109
00:08:05,930 --> 00:08:08,600
but suddenly, he had to go to a meeting. So...

110
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:12,430
Hadn't we agreed to do this move tomorrow? Why do it this suddenly?

111
00:08:12,990 --> 00:08:17,760
From what I see, he's acting kind on the outside but actually hateful on the inside. How petty.

112
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:22,450
The sooner you move back, the earlier President Ling's suspensed heart can finally calm down.

113
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:25,280
Then, I'll be going.

114
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,400
Be careful.

115
00:08:28,010 --> 00:08:30,800
- Be safe on the way back! 
 - You don't need to walk me out.

116
00:08:43,330 --> 00:08:45,390
That's it for today's meeting.

117
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:49,140
If you don't have anything to add, let's disperse the meeting.

118
00:08:50,450 --> 00:08:52,430
What's up, Anxin?

119
00:08:54,210 --> 00:08:56,490
Department Head, I have a

120
00:08:56,490 --> 00:08:59,580
an idea that isn't fully fleshed out that I'd like to get everyone's opinion on.

121
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,580
No problem. Then, let's look at it together.

122
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:04,260
Okay. I'll hold everyone up a few more minutes.

123
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:15,560
I'd like to make a story about a 9-headed bird who falls into the human realm 
  (T/N: The 9-headed bird was a legendary creature and early form of Chinese phoenix)

124
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:19,110
My inspiration comes from the 9-headed bird in the

125
00:09:19,110 --> 00:09:21,060
"Classic of Mountains and Seas," the 9-headed phoenix. 
  (T/N: Ancient compilation of all Chinese mythological creatures and geography)

126
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:25,250
Because I think two-dimensional art forms combined with traditional Chinese myths

127
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:27,860
can invite a new direction of modern trends.

128
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:30,510
I think we could try it out.

129
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:33,180
These are some new character images that I've created,

130
00:09:33,180 --> 00:09:35,290
and there are also some broad idea outlines.

131
00:09:41,890 --> 00:09:45,450
It doesn't seem like this style of drawing suits our company's audience.

132
00:09:45,450 --> 00:09:48,840
That's true, but I think Anxin's topic of selection

133
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,970
can be tried out.

134
00:09:50,970 --> 00:09:54,640
However, the target audience for this style of selection is too niche.

135
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:56,970
Moreover, it doesn't conform to the taste of today's youth.

136
00:09:56,970 --> 00:09:58,990
Have you done marketing research?

137
00:09:58,990 --> 00:10:02,180
She definitely hasn't. This isn't even a sector of the market.

138
00:10:02,180 --> 00:10:04,980
Besides, these demonstration sketches are far too crude.

139
00:10:08,090 --> 00:10:11,880
Our company has indeed not used this kind of idea before,

140
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:14,680
but I see that this theme is quite original.

141
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:16,970
It's not that we can't do it.

142
00:10:18,380 --> 00:10:21,110
How about this? Anxin, right now,

143
00:10:21,110 --> 00:10:23,270
upload ten episodes and we'll look at the results.

144
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:25,690
Do you have the confidence to do this?

145
00:10:25,690 --> 00:10:28,210
I'd like to try it.

146
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:39,220
Ling Yue!

147
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,090

148
00:10:42,090 --> 00:10:45,290
I have to work overtime today. You should go home first.

149
00:10:45,290 --> 00:10:47,820
Why do you have to work overtime again? Did your boss arrange more work for you?

150
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:51,510
No. It's that I haven't finished the work I was arranged to do.

151
00:10:52,910 --> 00:10:54,910
Then, how late will you be working?

152
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:57,250
I think it might take until early morning.

153
00:10:57,250 --> 00:11:01,300
Don't wait for me. If you're down here waiting for me, I won't be in the right mood to work.

154
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:03,310
It's so unsafe for a girl like you to work until the early hours of the day.

155
00:11:03,310 --> 00:11:06,280
It's fine. Our company's security is quite good.

156
00:11:07,070 --> 00:11:10,630
What's good about it? I haven't seen even one security guard.

157
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:15,480
Enough. Don't be so long-winded. Go on back, okay?

158
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,440
I'll watch you get in.

159
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:23,490
- Bye-bye. 
 - Bye-bye.

160
00:12:23,850 --> 00:12:28,120
Why are you still here?  You didn't wait here all night, did you?

161
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,640
How could I do that?  Do I have that much free time?

162
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,390
Quick, get in!

163
00:12:41,090 --> 00:12:43,520
Here, eat your breakfast.

164
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:48,340
Have you eaten?

165
00:12:58,250 --> 00:12:59,950
Eat more.

166
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:08,150
I have to eat quickly. I have to get back up there after I finish eating.

167
00:13:08,150 --> 00:13:10,140
You still have to work?

168
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:12,720
You can't sleep a little while?

169
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,730
How could I sleep?

170
00:13:16,290 --> 00:13:19,460
I have a blanket in the car. Sleep awhile.

171
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:23,930
You said you didn't wait for me. If you weren't waiting for me, where did this blanket come from?

172
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:28,180
Then look at who I am.

173
00:13:28,180 --> 00:13:30,770
I am the best boyfriend.

174
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:40,940
My boyfriend is so cute.

175
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:46,450
I haven't brushed my teeth.

176
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:49,170
It's fine. I haven't brushed mine either.

177
00:13:57,500 --> 00:14:01,910
 Gu Anxin, what right do you have to be so happy?

178
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:17,550
  Gu Anxin, you can do this.

179
00:14:17,550 --> 00:14:19,290
  Don't be a coward.

180
00:14:24,450 --> 00:14:27,390

181
00:14:39,610 --> 00:14:42,870
Did you see the data on The Alluring Nine-Headed Phoenix this morning?

182
00:14:42,870 --> 00:14:46,120
I saw it, I saw it. I can't believe Anxin is so capable.

183
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:49,560
She just released more than ten chapters and it's already at the top of the rankings online.

184
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:51,160
First time in history.

185
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:55,020
What? Surely you can see through this fakery?

186
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:57,650
She obviously bought that data.

187
00:14:58,510 --> 00:15:00,710
She brought her first place online ranking?

188
00:15:00,710 --> 00:15:04,760
No way! Normal people don't have the ability.

189
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:06,930
Of course, normal people don't have the ability.

190
00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:11,220
Our paratrooper here has New Way's president backing her up.

191
00:15:11,220 --> 00:15:12,830
The rumors are true?

192
00:15:12,830 --> 00:15:15,740
I heard the boss reporting to New Way's president this morning.

193
00:15:15,740 --> 00:15:18,600
The original numbers weren't even that high before.

194
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,230
I didn't expect...

195
00:15:20,230 --> 00:15:23,410
Anxin would have such support backing her.

196
00:15:23,410 --> 00:15:24,780
Otherwise, what would you have thought?

197
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:27,970
How could an ignorant rookie like her join our company otherwise?

198
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:29,820
So many artists can't even get in.

199
00:15:29,820 --> 00:15:31,820
You see, people are greedy.

200
00:15:31,820 --> 00:15:34,160
Originally, the data for The Alluring Nine-Headed Phoenix wasn't bad,

201
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:36,640
but she insisted on becoming first on the web.

202
00:15:48,950 --> 00:15:51,850
I'm sorry for taking up your time.

203
00:15:51,850 --> 00:15:55,310
Although I'm a rookie, I definitely won't buy data.

204
00:15:55,310 --> 00:15:57,740
I will go investigate this.

205
00:15:57,740 --> 00:15:59,310
I'm sorry.

206
00:16:08,530 --> 00:16:12,120
Hello, if you don't have an entrance card, you may not enter.

207
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:14,230
Then please help me notify them that I'm looking for your President Ling.

208
00:16:14,230 --> 00:16:16,560
Please give me your ID.

209
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,360
Anxin?

210
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:23,740
You came just in time. Do you have an entrance card? They're not letting me enter.

211
00:16:23,740 --> 00:16:26,300
I don't need it. I use my face.

212
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,200
What's going on with you two?

213
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:31,720
This is your future Lady Boss of New Way.

214
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:33,750
It's all his fault!

215
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:36,460
I told you to let the Lady Boss go in. What were you doing, you—

216
00:16:36,460 --> 00:16:39,480
- When did you say that? 
 - What about it?

217
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,590
 What did I do?

218
00:16:47,860 --> 00:16:50,130
Let's talk in private.

219
00:16:52,410 --> 00:16:55,000
You two may leave first.

220
00:17:04,610 --> 00:17:07,710
Why did you come? Did you miss me?

221
00:17:09,810 --> 00:17:13,010
There are some things that are not appropriate to say over the phone.

222
00:17:13,010 --> 00:17:15,070
What words?

223
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:19,130
Was my entry to Brilliant Worldly Culture your arrangement?

224
00:17:21,030 --> 00:17:22,890
You know all of it already?

225
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:27,290
So this morning's The Alluring Nine-Headed Phoenix

226
00:17:27,950 --> 00:17:30,240
data was all bought by you, right?

227
00:17:32,370 --> 00:17:34,070
Yes.

228
00:17:38,480 --> 00:17:40,870
The truth is that I kept thinking,

229
00:17:42,290 --> 00:17:45,060
as long as I kept working hard,

230
00:17:45,060 --> 00:17:48,150
even if it's slow or even slower,

231
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:51,900
I will eventually become a talented manga artist

232
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:53,880
using my own abilities.

233
00:17:55,050 --> 00:17:58,820
But why did you let all this happen so quickly?

234
00:17:58,820 --> 00:18:02,260
I'm still not qualified to have all this yet.

235
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:04,640
I'm sorry.

236
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:07,150
I didn't hide it from you on purpose.

237
00:18:07,150 --> 00:18:10,650
I just wanted you to focus on doing what you liked.

238
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:14,820
Even without me, you could still use your abilities to join Brilliant Worldly Culture.

239
00:18:14,820 --> 00:18:17,990
I merely added wood to stoke the fire for you. You must believe in yourself.

240
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:20,510
This is not the problem of adding wood.

241
00:18:20,510 --> 00:18:24,490
You built a stairway of clouds to bring me up to the sky.

242
00:18:24,490 --> 00:18:28,680
The higher I fly, the worse it will hurt to fall. Don't you understand this logic?

243
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,660
Compared to silently releasing an entire series at home,

244
00:18:30,660 --> 00:18:33,660
wouldn't going to an honorable company to work and do the things you enjoy

245
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:36,200
be killing two birds with one stone?

246
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:38,090
Honorable?

247
